// §5.9 branch narrowing — positive (is undefined, is null) and
// inverse (is not type T, is not named tag) forms swap then/else
// from the base cases. Test that each form drives the correct branch.

// Case 1: `is undefined` — positive form
undef_val is nonexistent
classify_missing is if undef_val is undefined
    then "unset"
    else "set"

// Case 2: `is null` — positive form
some_optional is null
classify_optional is if some_optional is null
    then "empty"
    else "has value"

// Case 3: `is not type T` — inverse of is type
U is union i32, string
val is "hello" as U
kind is if val is not type i32
    then "not integer"
    else "integer"

// Case 4: `is not named tag` — inverse of is named
Result is tagged union ok as string, err as string
r is "fail" as Result named err
status is if r is not named ok
    then "error path"
    else "success path"
